The paper deals with the characterization of the $\eta$-Nash equilibrium region of the interference channel with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The interference channel is a type of networked system, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses coding schemes and achievable information rate pairs, which are topics in signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents a generalization of existing results, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
